HEADWORD: Queencraft
<hw>Queen"craft`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Craft or skill in
policy on the part of a queen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Elizabeth showed much <qex>queencraft</qex> in procuring the votes
of the nobility.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

